{"summary":"Accept the targeted removal of legacy-only compatibility code and tests, and accept the fix to use attempt start time when matching starts. Reject the amendment that deletes `started_at` instead of using it, and reject the broader schema-hardening amendment because it would make legitimately-unknown fields fail validation.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-14-b5a477a3","decision":"accept","rationale":"`milestone_id` is supplied on every lineage-store write path, so keeping it optional plus backfill/canonicalization only hides malformed current rows. Making it required and removing the repair logic strengthens the on-disk contract and surfaces bad writes immediately."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-c5bceaec","decision":"accept","rationale":"Completion journal details are written as structured JSON in current code. The comma-delimited legacy parser and replacement branch only serve hypothetical old data and can mask serialization regressions in new writes instead of failing fast."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-1ac821d9","decision":"accept","rationale":"The named deserialization/backfill tests exist only to preserve legacy-schema behavior that should disappear with the corresponding compatibility code. Removing them is correct once that code is removed; the `skipped_beads` test should only be dropped if that field is intentionally made required."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-89e13c37","decision":"reject","rationale":"`started_at` is not merely unused cleanup surface. It is the only fallback attempt identifier when `run_id` is absent or arrives later, so deleting it would lock in the current matching bug rather than fixing it."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-c6ca5e53","decision":"reject","rationale":"The fail-fast direction is right for missing `milestone_id` and legacy journal repair, but this amendment is too broad. Not every optional/defaulted field here is legacy-only: `run_id`, `plan_hash`, `outcome_detail`, and `finished_at` can all be legitimately absent on current rows, so treating all such omissions as schema defects would overconstrain valid data."},{"amendment_id":"fr-14-ec2442bd","decision":"accept","rationale":"`find_matching_running_task_run` currently ignores `started_at`, so it cannot distinguish an idempotent replay of the same attempt from a genuinely new runless retry, and it also misses the case where the same attempt is replayed later with a newly known `run_id`. Using start time as the fallback discriminator fixes both the silent-collapse and phantom-running-row failures."}]}